name: The last Photo of Jamenson Family
description: his is the latest photograph of the Jameson Family, missing in Red Oak Forest in 2009. Body parts were found in the forest by hunters found in November 2013 and positively identified by Oklahoma medical examiner on July 3, 2014. No cause of death was determined and the circumstances surrounding his disappearance remain unknown. This is a fictional background for my 3d creature. This photograph was found in the remains left by the family's camp. Digitally restored due to the poor condition of the device, it was the sharpest image that seems to show some kind of giant simian creature, which may or may not be related to the deaths of the entire family.
